<subSubSection id="0727D1574257F793DA0EFF3AA35DDBAF" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" type="description">
<paragraph id="21AFF8059D64B8427EBD37FEB037631A" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3185ECEA27B4A5F750605DF200A3CE64" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">
Perennial herb from a woody rootstock with stems to at least 40 cm, the whole plant densely but very shortly tomentose leaving leaf veins visible; branches somewhat woody. Lower leaves c. 8 
<normalizedToken id="1D13EE6C3E7CAAAC30486C3FCF4C7708" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 cm, oblanceolate, narrowed to a long petiole-like base; stem leaves 2.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="59692EE8DAB72029D044AF9154948A84" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.5 cm, ovate, obtuse, margin entire, base cordate and subsessile. Flowers in dense axillary heads, sessile above, shortly pedunculate below; bracts 1.3-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="53CB36296B52B73015B9D1B284A5BE01" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1-2.2 cm, ovate, acuminate, basally cordate; peduncles 0-1.5 cm; bracteoles 10-15 
<normalizedToken id="A10D3227230AEB31BBA59942D8E01DB6" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, linear, long-pilose; pedicels absent; outer sepals 14-16 
<normalizedToken id="17B5989A160AAB66D3096909170A099C" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4 mm, ovate, abruptly narrowed, rounded and with a long, aristate point, long pilose; inner sepals somewhat smaller, c. 12 
<normalizedToken id="83B9E01E0730851C34E0A7F5A49987E7" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-3 mm; corolla 1.5-1.8 cm, pink, midpetaline bands long-pilose; ovary comose; style glabrous, divided c. 6 mm above base, stigma 3 mm; capsule not seen. [
<bibRefCitation id="383E35F477F037B46960BACB755CC97D" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="C5F49B606ADF7083AD096EF7A28A51BE" originalValue="Saâ€™ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 155; 
<bibRefCitation id="7F72A3A30E15B6FB99AE89A1F8E07901" author="Nowroozi, M" journalOrPublisher="Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 110" refId="B244" refString="Nowroozi, M, 2002. Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae. Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran: 1 - 110" title="Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae" year="2002">Nowroozi 2002</bibRefCitation>
: 75 (plate), 104 (map)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5112C081F27A5D3BC8E5DB17D80BC7F4" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BC80C98D2502AAB9F5419FCBABF1CF09" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D897E0FED5169242D0BD14E793770C4C" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">
Endemic to Iran (
<emphasis id="07234BD5290B664C15E6A207EDB9478A" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Stapf</emphasis>
373, 
<emphasis id="1A64520EB219AD538E3332D740328CD3" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Haussknecht</emphasis>
s.n. [4/1868], 
<emphasis id="E1A4C87A8804249B6C033A1F762E9BEB" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Stutz</emphasis>
984). Apparently rare.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8E07628C6E0C41A60A7ED714310F888B" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" type="notes">
